  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/83",
  "title": "Widget events ",
  "body": "Here's what we could do to be able to have events on widgets. Like `refine` \n\n**app.js**\n\n``` js\nvar instantsearch = require('instantsearch');\nvar search = instantsearch(...);\nvar refinementList = instantsearch.widgets.refinementList(...);\nvar slider = instantsearch.widgets.slider(...);\n\nrefinementList.on('refine', function(newValue, previousValue) {});\nslider.on('slide');\nslider.on('change');\n\nsearch.addWidget(refinementList);\nsearch.addWidget(slider);\n```\n\n**Widget.js**\n\n``` js\nvar EventEmitter = require('events');\nclass Widget extends EventEmitter {}\n\nWidget.utils = {\n  getContainerNode() {}\n}\n\nmodule.exports = Widget;\n```\n\n**IndexSelector.js**\n\n``` js\nvar toFactory  = require('to-factory');\nvar React = require('react');\n\nvar Widget = require('../Widget');\n\nclass IndexSelector extends Widget {\n  getConfiguraition(){}\n  init(){}\n  render(){}\n}\n\n// can use this.emit(); at any time\n// can use Widget.utils.getContainerNode of course\n\n// allows to use indexSelector() instead of new `IndexSelector()`\nmodule.exports = toFactory(Widget);\n```\n\nFor people to build their own eventful widgets (non events widgets is not an issue here) outside of a browserify/webpack env (where it's easy to extend EventEmitter): we can expose utils in instantsearch namespace like [inherits](https://nodejs.org/docs/latest/api/util.html#util_util_inherits_constructor_superconstructor) and [EventEmitter](https://nodejs.org/api/events.html#events_class_events_eventemitter).\n",
